<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2017-08-10</DATELINE><TITLE>New episode of Middle East Respiratory Syndrome Coronavirus outbreak in Saudi Arabia: an emerging public health threat</TITLE><BODY>• Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus (MERS-CoV) is resurgent in Saudi Arabia. • Intercontinental travel facilitates the spread of MERS-CoV infection to other global locations. • Improved vigilance is imperative to curb the dissemination of infection. • Discovery of an effective therapy and prophylaxis is a public health priority.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>